SIMPLE: save
RECORDS: 5

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Save
<hw>Save</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Sage</er> the
herb.]</ety> <def>The herb sage, or salvia.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Save</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Save
<hw>Save</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Saved</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Saving</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE. <ets>saven</ets>,
<ets>sauven</ets>, <ets>salven</ets>, OF. <ets>salver</ets>,
<ets>sauver</ets>, F. <ets>sauver</ets>, L. <ets>salvare</ets>, fr.
<ets>salvus</ets> saved, safe. See <er>Safe</er>, <pos>a.</pos>]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>To make safe; to procure the safety of; to preserve
from injury, destruction, or evil of any kind; to rescue from impending
danger; <as>as, to <ex>save</ex> a house from the flames</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>God <qex>save</qex> all this fair company.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He cried, saying, Lord, <qex>save</qex> me.</q> <rj><qau>Matt.
xiv. 30.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Thou hast . . . quitted all to <qex>save</qex>⟦br⟧
A world from utter loss.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Theol.)</fld> <def>Specifically, to deliver from
sin and its penalty; to rescue from a state of condemnation and
spiritual death, and bring into a state of spiritual life.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Christ Jesus came into the world to <qex>save</qex> sinners.</q>
<rj><qau>1 Tim. i. 15.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To keep from being spent or lost; to secure from
waste or expenditure; to lay up; to reserve.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Now save a nation, and now <qex>save</qex> a groat.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>To rescue from something undesirable or hurtful; to
prevent from doing something; to spare.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I'll <qex>save</qex> you⟦br⟧
That labor, sir. All's now done.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>To hinder from doing, suffering, or happening; to
obviate the necessity of; to prevent; to spare.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Will you not speak to <qex>save</qex> a lady's blush?</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>6.</sn> <def>To hold possession or use of; to escape loss
of.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Just <qex>saving</qex> the tide, and putting in a stock of
merit.</q> <rj><qau>Swift.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>To save appearances</b></col>, <cd>to preserve a decent
outside; to avoid exposure of a discreditable state of
things.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To preserve; rescue; deliver; protect; spare;
reserve; prevent.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Save</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Save
<hw>Save</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To avoid unnecessary expense or
expenditure; to prevent waste; to be economical.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Brass ordnance <qex>saveth</qex> in the quantity of the
material.</q> <rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Save</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Save
<hw>Save</hw>, <pos>prep. ⟦or⟧ conj.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>sauf</ets>,
properly adj., safe. See <er>Safe</er>, <pos>a.</pos>]</ety>
<def>Except; excepting; not including; leaving out; deducting;
reserving; saving.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Five times received I forty stripes <qex>save</qex> one.</q>
<rj><qau>2 Cor. xi. 24.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- See <er>Except</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Save</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 5 ====
HEADWORD: Save
<hw>Save</hw>, <pos>conj.</pos> <def>Except; unless.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Saveable</ent>⟦br⟧
